result.execSummary:
The defendant Steven J. KHAIL was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manufacture/Deliver Heroin (<3g),, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(d)1.
  • Manufacture/Deliver Heroin (<3g),, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(d)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Defendant in custody and appearing by video from the Manitowoc County Jail.  The State informs the Court that the defendant will be charged with the crimes of 5 counts of deliver heroin, as a repeater, possession with intent to deliver heroin, and fleeing an officer.  The matters are continued for initial appearance on 11/02/2015.  Bail is set at $4,000.00 cash bond with the conditions that he report to the Manitowoc County Sheriff's Department for fingerprints, photographs and other identifying information within 24 hours of release.   Bail not furnished and defendant is remanded to the county jail, commitment for failure to furnish bail issued.
